-- S.Korean stocks, won edge down on Ukraine jitters
-- By Christine Kim
-- Mon Apr 21, 2014 02:08AM EDT
-- None



SEOUL, April 21 (Reuters) - Seoul shares and the South Korean won <KRW=> both slipped on Monday as investors remained cautious over tensions in Ukraine, but most chose to keep to the sidelines in the absence of cues as several markets were still closed for Easter holiday.

The Korea Composite Stock Price Index (KOSPI) <.KS11> closed down 0.3 percent at 1,999.22.